What you need to know:

In Uganda, opposition voices to a prolonged economy lock-down lasting over one year- started emerging in the last quarter of 2021 with arguments that the economy that only grew by 3.8% in 2021 was on the brink.The Omicron Covid-19 variant has wreaked havoc throughout the festive season in several parts of the world with the world December 30 topping one million overnight cases.